benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Add tags to bundle

covered: Valid Payload coverage across TC01–TC07 (successful creation with valid payloads, including single and multiple tags and empty tag list)
Invalid Payload coverage (malformed JSON, non-array body, invalid UUIDs, extra fields) across TC10, TC11, TC12, TC15, TC18
Non-Existent Resource / Invalid bundle id handling (TC08 invalid format, TC09 non-existent bundle)
Authorization and header validation (TC13 missing header, TC16 missing/invalid token)
Empty tag list handling (TC07: empty array results in 201 with no tags)
Duplicate tag handling (TC26 avoids duplicate Tag objects)
Large payloads and limits (TC20 maximum payload, TC21 payload too large)
Service unavailability / backend failure (TC17 503, TC22 timeout scenarios)
Performance testing (TC24 normal load, TC25 peak load with concurrency)
Integration tests (TC27 GET verification post, TC28 cross-service data consistency)
Accessibility test (TC29) covering API documentation accessibility
gaps: Rate limiting tests (throttling and bursts) are not covered
403 Forbidden scenarios (insufficient permissions beyond 401/missing token) not explicitly tested
Internal server error coverage beyond 503 (e.g., 500) not covered
Additional negative tests for header value validation and edge-case payload structures not exhaustively covered
recommendations: Add a test for 403 Forbidden to verify proper handling when permissions are insufficient
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling scenarios to validate system behavior under bursts
Add caching-related tests to verify ETag and Cache-Control headers where applicable
Include 500 Internal Server Error scenario coverage in addition to 503
Expand negative tests for header values and edge-case payload formats (e.g., unusual characters, extremely large strings)
Consider more concurrency-heavy TC25 variants or targeted stress tests for high-load conditions
